content:
The Model Management page shows metrics on the quality of your bot’s intent model and individual intent details. Use the information to fine-tune intents and improve how well your bot understands your customers.

Einstein Bots is available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience. Setup for Einstein Bots is available in Lightning Experience.
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

To build and manage Einstein Bots, you need the following permissions:

Customize Application
Modify Metadata
Manage Bots

Your bot is only as good as the data that you feed it. To ensure Bot quality, we recommend visiting the Model Management menu often.

The F1 score combines precision and recall metrics to show how accurate the model is at predicting correctly.
Precision: correct positive results divided by total positive results
Recall: positive results divided by total expected results

To improve your intent’s F1 score:

Add utterances and clarify intents
Frequently integrate new customer data from conversation transcripts
Rebuild the model if it pre-dates the F1 score integration

To act on recommendations, click Edit Intent or use the Einstein Intent Assessor AppExchange tool.
To view model performance in other languages, click Download Model Metrics.
title: Evaluating Einstein Bots Performance
